snippet.textDisplay:
Wow, you got the Gamestop story entirely wrong.

Brokers have been shorting it for years, to an absurd degree, continually pushing the value down below what it should be.  Someone noticed, and decide to see if something could be done about it.  And the easiest way to punish sleazy stock shorters is to push the value of the stock up, and that can be done simply by buying it en masse.

All the brokers losing money on the short position are bad guys, without exception.  They deserve to lose all that money.

The normies buying the stock are the good guys.  They're not likely to make any money at all, but the most they stand to lose is their initial investment, unlike the brokers.
snippet.textOriginal:
